bio: Scott has worked on a large variety of systems over his career. He tested the logic in the Boeing 777 autopilot, built software to run refrigerated warehouses, created a system to transmit medical data from an ambulance to the hospital, and built building door management systems. On Azure, he helped build a scalable actuarial modeling system and delivered a kiosk based movie rental system. At Microsoft, he has worked on WCF, Service Bus, and Notification Hubs. He used his breadth of knowledge to co-author five books, speak at user groups across the US, and teach for Pluralsight and Wintellect. Today, he spends his time helping Microsoft customers in financial services understand how to use Azure.
